Excerpt from EUnet Press Release, Feb, 1997

EUnet is pleased to announce that EUnetTraveller is now also available in Sweden with a point of presence (POP) in Stockholm and in the Czech Republic with POPs in Hradec Kralove, Jablonec n. N., Liberec, Most, Nachod, Nachod, Olomouc, Prague, Usti nad Labem. (Several POPs in CZ are still unaccessible, but will be activated soon.)

You can find the latest numbers on the WWW page:

http://traveller.EU.net/html/pops.html

or send an empty email to traveller@EU.net. The latter is a mail robot and will return you the latest POP access list. It's handy to keep this list on your laptop, in case you need to dial into EUnetTraveller in a foreign country.

For all further inquiries you can contact the EUnetTraveller Call Centre: traveller-info@EU.net or ring +32.16-39 80 80 during normal business hours from Monday to Friday.

Thank you for choosing EUnetTraveller.

The EUnetTraveller team.
